value.value: Aspartate aminotransferase, cytoplasmic (413 aa, ~46 kDa) is encoded by the human GOT1 gene. This protein is involved in amino acid metabolism.
This gene is involved in the tricarboxylic acid cycle, urea cycle and amino acid metabolism.
Aspartate aminotransferase, mitochondrial (430 aa, ~48 kDa) is encoded by the human GOT2 gene. This protein plays a role in both the metabolism of amino acids and fatty acid transport.
This gene is involved in amino acid metabolism and liver gluconeogenesis.
Inflammation of the colon that is only apparent by microscopic examination.
Alanine aminotransferase 1 (496 aa, ~55 kDa) is encoded by the human GPT gene. This protein plays a role in both amino acid metabolism and pyruvate synthesis.
This gene plays a role in amino acid metabolism, liver gluconeogenesis and the homeostasis of fatty acid metabolism and storage.
Alanine aminotransferase 2 (523 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human GPT2 gene. This protein is involved in both pyruvate biosynthesis and amino acid metabolism.
A malignant neoplasm that shows clinical and/or pathologic progression.
Any component of the organ that is part of the hematopoietic and immune systems consisting of white and red pulp within the left hypochondriac region.
This gene is involved in the metabolism of nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids in the cytosol.
Thymidine kinase, cytosolic (234 aa, ~25 kDa) is encoded by the human TK1 gene. This protein plays a role in pyrimidine metabolism.
Thymidine kinase 2, mitochondrial (265 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human TK2 gene. This protein is involved in mitochondrial pyrimidine metabolism.
This gene plays a role in mitochondrial DNA synthesis in non-replicating cells.
The lymphoid tissue of the thymus in which T cell maturation occurs.
Nodules of lymphoid tissue located on either side of the back of the nasal canal and throat.
This gene plays a regulatory role in receptor-mediated endocytosis and iron metabolism.
Lymphoid tissue of the tonsils. It is composed of B and T lymphocytes. Lymphoid follicles with germinal centers occupy the areas that are populated with B lymphocytes.
Transferrin receptor protein 1 (760 aa, ~85 kDa) is encoded by the human TFRC gene. This protein plays a role in the transport of iron into cells.
Any of the mental or physical manifestations that accompany perimenopause and menopause.
This gene plays a role in iron metabolism.
Transferrin receptor protein 2 (801 aa, ~89 kDa) is encoded by the human TFR2 gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of cellular uptake of transferrin-iron complexes.
This gene is involved in the mediation of gene transcription and regulation of signal transduction.

label.value: Serine/Threonine Protein Phosphatase 2B Catalytic Subunit Alpha Isoform

value.value: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase 2B catalytic subunit alpha isoform (521 aa, ~59 kDa) is encoded by the human PPP3CA gene. This protein is involved in calmodulin binding, protein dephosphorylation and signal transduction.
This gene plays a role in calcium ion-dependent processes in the mitochondria and the regulation of signal transduction.

label.value: Serine/Threonine Protein Phosphatase 2B Catalytic Subunit Beta Isoform

value.value: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase 2B catalytic subunit beta isoform (524 aa, ~59 kDa) is encoded by the human PPP3CB gene. This protein plays a role in metal binding, signal transduction, calmodulin binding and protein dephosphorylation.
This gene is involved in the regulation of signal transduction.

label.value: Serine/Threonine Protein Phosphatase 2B Catalytic Subunit Gamma Isoform

value.value: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase 2B catalytic subunit gamma isoform (512 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human PPP3CC gene. This protein is involved in protein dephosphorylation, calmodulin binding, and apoptotic signaling.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction. It is also involved in the differentiation of osteoblasts.
Calcineurin subunit B type 1 (170 aa, ~19 kDa) is encoded by the human PPP3R1 gene. This protein plays a role in both calcineurin regulation and apoptotic signaling pathways.
Inflammation of the mucous membranes lining the gastrointestinal tract.
This gene plays a role in calcium-mediated signal transduction.
Calcineurin subunit B type 2 (170 aa, ~20 kDa) is encoded by the human PPP3R2 gene. This protein is involved in both protein dephosphorylation and osteoblast differentiation.
The faculty of vision, the perception of objects by the eye.

Ubiquitously or widely expressed human CREB Family Genes (bZIP/CREB Family) encode conserved cAMP Responsive Element Binding Proteins, nuclear bZIP domain dimeric transcription factors that bind to octameric DNA palindrome cAMP-response elements (CRE) present in many viral and cellular promoters and induce gene transcription in response to cAMP signaling pathways. CREB proteins bind to DNA as a homodimer or a heterodimer with JUN/c-Jun or ATF2/CREBP1. Increased cAMP levels following stimulation activate cAMP-dependent protein kinase A, which phosphorylates CREB proteins that stimulate transcription of cAMP-responsive genes.  Calcium-regulated CREB transcription factors integrate calcium and cAMP signals.  cAMP pathways provide a chief means by which cellular growth, differentiation, and function can be influenced by extracellular signals. (NCI)
The faculty of touch, the sensation produced by pressure receptors in the skin.
This gene is involved in transcriptional regulation and its activity is modulated in response to hormonal stimulation from the cAMP pathway.
Cyclic AMP-responsive element-binding protein 1 (341 aa, ~37 kDa) is encoded by the human CREB1 gene. This protein plays a role in transcriptional regulation.
This gene is involved in transcription and mediates DNA-binding interactions.

Cyclic AMP-responsive element-binding protein 3 (395 aa, ~44 kDa) is encoded by the human CREB3 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of transcription downstream of regulated intramembrane proteolysis.
This gene is involved in transcriptional activation.

Cyclic AMP-responsive element-binding protein 3-like protein 4 (395 aa, ~43 kDa) is encoded by the human CREB3L4 gene. This protein plays a role in both the response to unfolded proteins and transcription.
This gene plays a role in cAMP response element-dependent transcriptional activation.
Cyclic AMP-responsive element-binding protein 5 (508 aa, ~57 kDa) is encoded by the human CREB5 gene. This protein is involved in transcriptional regulation.
This gene is involved in the initiation of protein synthesis.

label.value: Translation Initiation Factor EIF-2B Subunit Alpha

value.value: Translation initiation factor eIF-2B subunit alpha (305 aa, ~34 kDa) is encoded by the human EIF2B1 gene. This protein plays a role in both the regulation of protein synthesis and guanine nucleotide exchange.
This gene plays a role in the regulation of protein translation.

label.value: Translation Initiation Factor EIF-2B Subunit Beta

value.value: Translation initiation factor eIF-2B subunit beta (351 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human EIF2B2 gene. This protein is involved in both GDP-GTP exchange and protein synthesis.
This gene is involved in both the initiation and regulation of protein synthesis.
